MetaDescription: Create marketing automation workflows that connect your MailChimp lists & campaigns to your business applications.
Content:
Integrate MailChimp

Connect MailChimp to many other apps without code

One of the world’s largest email marketing platforms, MailChimp offers a wide array of email marketing tools that allow you to dip your toes into the world of marketing automation by creating beautiful email campaigns that can be tailored to your contact lists.

These email lists and campaigns create a lot of data, telling you who’s engaged with your brand and what they are interested in, but how can you make use of it to optimise other areas of your business?

Cyclr's easy to use builder lets you drag and drop to integrate MailChimp with many popular apps. In a few clicks you can connect MailChimp to your CRM, ecommerce platform, event booking, and much more.

Case Studies Pre-made Integrations Features Request a Demo
Case Studies

How Cyclr integrates and automates MailChimp

CRM and Email Marketing Automation


Your CRM holds the keys to your sales. You use it to manage contacts, track leads, run projects, record sales - it is your business. Combining this data with your MailChimp email marketing platform allows you to create far more tailor made campaigns by managing your email marketing lists more accurately.

Cyclr’s drag and drop workflow builder allows you to link, sync and automate process between your favourite Cloud platforms. Ensure your sales and marketing teams are effectively working together by adding automated processes between their prefered systems.

Set Up Your Pre & Post Event Marketing Campaigns Well in Advance

Automatically manage post-show attendee and non-attendee messages well in advance - allowing your team to focus on the event itself - by making the most of marketing automation.

Cyclr’s workflow builder allows you to create automation rules that handle your customers data from the moment they register to your event. Automatically create mailing lists in your MailChimp account for attendees and non-attendees, send messages during the event or handle exhibitor re-bookings for your next show.

Automated Mailing List Management - Keeping Your Data Clean

On top of data generated from your email marketing campaigns your business gathers far more data about your customers from other sources. Whether it is from enquiries from your website, updated CRM records, event attendance or support tickets, you find out more & more about what your customers are interested in.

This data can all be combined to create narrow, niche customer lists; so you can improve your klout with your customers by sending them only relevant email campaigns that are focused on their needs and wants. As their requirements change you need a way to adapt to their new needs, which makes managing your lists an even more timely and important task.
